title: What do the values K >>1 and K <<1 imply about a reaction? - Quora

response.answer_text: Hi K>>1 that's mean concentration of reactions materials (or numbers of moles ) higher than products materials. k<<1 that's mean concentration of products materials higher than reactions materials. K =1 concentration of reactions materials equal to products materials. K=[concentration of reactions materials] / [concentration of products materials]
